tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE user_mouse_movements (
  user_id INT NOT NULL,
  x_movement INT NOT NULL,
  y_movement INT NOT NULL,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (user_id)
);

CREATE TABLE user_profile (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(50),
  typing_speed FLOAT,
  mouse_movements JSON
)

CREATE TABLE typing_speed_logs (
  log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  typing_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  typing_speed FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE mouse_movements_logs (
  log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  movement_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  distance_moved FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE biometric_analysis (
  analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  analysis_date DATE,
  biometric_data JSON
)
CREATE TABLE user (user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,name VARCHAR(50), typing_speed INT, mouse_movements INT);
CREATE TABLE typing_speed (typing_id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, speed INT, timestamp TIMESTAMP);
CREATE TABLE mouse_movements (movement_id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, distance INT, duration INT, timestamp TIMESTAMP);
CREATE TABLE biometric_analysis (analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, analysis_result VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP);
CREATE TABLE user_session (session_id INT PRIMARY KEY, user_id INT, start_time TIMESTAMP, end_time TIMESTAMP);
